Step 1: Create a Static CSS File
yourapp/
├── static/
│   └── css/
│       └── styles.css

Example: styles.css
/* styles.css */

body {
    font-family: 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
    background-color: #fdfdfd;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    color: #333;
}

header, nav {
    background-color: #2c3e50;
    color: white;
    padding: 15px;
    text-align: center;
}

nav ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 30px;
}

nav ul li a {
    color: white;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: bold;
}

nav ul li a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
}

.container {
    max-width: 960px;
    margin: 40px auto;
    padding: 20px;
    background: white;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
}

h1, h2 {
    color: #2c3e50;
}

footer {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 20px;
    background-color: #ecf0f1;
    color: #666;
    margin-top: 50px;
}

Step 2: Load Static Files in Template
# settings.py
STATIC_URL = '/static/'

{% load static %}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>{% block title %}Home{% endblock %}</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="{% static 'css/styles.css' %}">
</head>
<body>
    {% block content %}{% endblock %}
</body>
</html>

Step 3: Wrap Homepage Content
{% extends 'base.html' %}
{% block title %}Welcome{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<div class="container">
    <h1>Welcome to Our Restaurant</h1>
    <p>Enjoy delicious meals and great service!</p>
</div>
{% endblock %}


Result:
Clean modern font and layout
Styled header and nav
Padded, centered content
Professional, minimal color scheme